topic.title: LVCMOS DC Characteristics

entry.p: DC Sourcing Current (Maximum DC current sourcing capability
DC Sinking Current (Maximum DC current sink capability

li.p: Specification for both with and without Schmitt Trigger.
The maximum DC current drive is obtained by setting MODE=”11”. Under this mode, the IO can source/sink 12 mA average current for 10 years within the limits of acceptable EM degradation.
VOH/VOL is measured with the following conditions:

IOH/IOL values are the test load currents at which the logic level VOH/VOL are measured. This is only a method of defining VOH/VOL. JESD76 defines VOH=VDD – 0.45 and VOL = 0.45 for IOH/IOL = 2 mA (JESD76 Table 4.3) The IOH/IOL values mentioned above are NOT the actual DC currents supported for a lifetime of 10 years. The Electromigration limit determines the maximum current supported under various modes of operation. The DC current supported for a lifetime of 10 years is defined as ISOURCE(DC) and ISINK(DC).

Rpd values are valid for output voltage range from VOL to VDDO, and Rpu values are valid for output voltage range from 0 to VOH.
